SP.P:
Your grace shal find him in your further cōferēce Graue, wise, courtly, & scholler like, vnderstādingly read In the necessities of the life of man. He knowes that man is mortall by his birth; He knowes that men must dye, and therefore liue;

He knowes that man must liue, and therefore eate,
 And if it shall please your grace, to accompany your selfe with him, I doubt not, but that hee will at the least, make good my commendations.
